{"title_page": "Lucian Grainge", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=September 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- For individuals; see Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                = Sir Lucian Grainge\n| image                 =\n| alt             = \n| caption            = \n| image_size            = \n| background          = non_performing_personnel\n| birth_name          = Lucian Charles Grainge\n| alias               = \n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1960|2|29}}\n| birth_place         = {{Nowrap|London, England, United Kingdom}}\n| origin              = \n| instrument          = \n| genre               = \n| occupation          = Chairman & chief executive officer, [[Universal Music Group]]\n| years_active        = 1982\u2013present \n| label               = [[Universal Music Group]]\n| associated_acts     = \n| website                 = \n}}\n\n'''Sir Lucian Charles Grainge''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CBE}} (born 29 February 1960)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people/people-of-today/people-of-today-search-results.aspx?personId=22650&name=Lucian+Charles |title=Debrett's - The trusted source on British social skills, etiquette and style-Debrett's |website=Debretts.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref> is the chairman and chief executive officer of [[Universal Music Group]]. Over the course of his career, he has worked with artists including [[Amy Winehouse]], [[ABBA]], [[Eurythmics]], [[Rihanna (singer)|Rihanna]], [[Sam Smith (singer)|Sam Smith]], [[Take That]], [[Psychedelic Furs]], [[The Rolling Stones]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Jamie Cullum]] and [[Andrea Bocelli]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.grammy.com/news/pre-grammy-gala-to-honor-lucian-grainge|title= Pre-GRAMMY Gala To Honor Lucian Grainge |publisher= Grammy.com}}</ref><ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web |url= https://www.billboard.com/biz/6465255/lucian-grainge-the-2015-billboard-power-100 |title= Lucian Grainge: The 2015 Billboard Power 100 |publisher= Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.fmqb.com/article.asp?id=2891913 |title= Lucian Grainge Tops Billboard's 2015 Power 100 List |publisher= FMQB}}</ref> Grainge has worked in the music business for his entire career.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news| url=http://www.time.com/time/business/article/0,8599,1967817,00.html | work=Time | title=New Boss for Universal Music, Lady Gaga Record Label \u2013 TIME | date=3 March 2010}}</ref> Billboard magazine named Grainge as the most powerful person in the music business on four occasions in the 2010s, and the first-ever Executive of the Decade.<ref name=\"2019 power 100\">{{cite web |last1=Marks |first1=Craig |title=Billboard Power 100's New No. 1: Universal Music Group's Lucian Grainge |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8496609/power-100-lucian-grainge-no-1-universal-music-group |website=Billboard |accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8548431/lucian-grainge-power-executive-of-the-decade-interview|title=Lucian Grainge of Universal Music Group: Executive of the Decade|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> \n\n==Early life and career==\nGrainge grew up in [[North London]]. He was raised Jewish.<ref>https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/sir-lucian-grainge-we-must-keep-listening-to-new-ideas-through-young-ears/</ref> Grainge left [[Queen Elizabeth's Grammar School for Boys]] at the age of 18, and began working as a runner at MPC, a talent scout company.<ref name=autogenerated1 /> After contacting several record label bosses, he was offered a job by [[Maurice Oberstein]], chairman of [[CBS Records International|CBS Records]], working at publishing company April Music's A&R department. His first signing was [[The Psychedelic Furs]]. In 1982, he became the director of [[RCA Music]] Publishing. Two years later he became an A&R director for [[MCA Records]]. He set up PolyGram Music Publishing in 1986 and joined Polydor as general manager of A&R and business affairs in 1993. He was promoted to managing director of Polydor in 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/news/e3i6c8a99484479c6fe47cc255d753293b0 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-11-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110907164645/http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/news/e3i6c8a99484479c6fe47cc255d753293b0 |archivedate=7 September 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> \n\n==Universal Music Group==\nGrainge became the chairman of the UK division of the Universal Music Group, and then in 2005 of Universal Music Group International. He served in this position until 2010. On 1 January 2011 he became CEO of Universal Music Group, and then chairman on 9 March 2011, succeeding [[Doug Morris]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universalmusic.com/corporate/news35723 |title=Universal Music Group |website=Universalmusic.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref>\n\nWithin his first year as chairman & CEO of Universal, the company acquired [[EMI]]'s Recorded Music operations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/record-labels/emi-publishing-goes-to-sony-label-to-universal-1005508552.story |title=EMI Publishing Goes to Sony, Label to Universal &#124; Billboard |website=Billboard.biz |date=2011-11-11 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref> Grainge argued that selling to Universal was the only way to improve EMI, for the benefit of the entire industry.<ref name=\"Buzzfeed\">{{cite web |url = https://www.buzzfeed.com/richardmorgan/how-universal-music-ceo-lucian-grainge-became-the-most-power|title= How Universal Music CEO Lucian Grainge Became The Most Powerful Man in Music |publisher= Buzzfeed}}</ref> UMG subsequently attempted to revitalise former EMI labels including Capitol Records and Virgin Records.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/1083683/universal-music-ceo-lucian-grainge-says-hell-double-ar-investment-at |title=Universal Music CEO Lucian Grainge Says He'll 'Double A&R Investment' at Capitol, Virgin |publisher= Billboard}}</ref> Commenting on the EMI acquisition, [[Buzzfeed]] commented that \"Grainge will go down as the master architect of what is likely to be the last big deal in the music business\".<ref name=\"Buzzfeed\"/>\n\nAs chairman and Chief Executive of Universal, Grainge has also sought to increase the group's international digital expansion via distribution partnerships with technology companies, including [[Apple Inc.|Apple]], [[Spotify]], [[Facebook]], [[Tencent]], and [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/digital-and-mobile/apple-signs-deal-with-universal-music-group-1005213452.story |title=Apple Signs Deal With Universal Music Group for iCloud, Major Publishers Also on Board &#124; Billboard |website=Billboard.biz |date=2011-06-02 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/digital-and-mobile/universal-music-group-launching-spotify-1005293772.story |title=Universal Music Group Launching Spotify Playlist Service for U.S. Fans &#124; Billboard |website=Billboard.biz |date=2011-07-27 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20101001085211/http://corporate.sky.com/media/press_releases/2008/sky_to_partner_with_universal_music_for_innovative_new_digital_music_service.htm]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universalmusic.com/corporate/universal-music-group-expands-digsterfm-with-rdio-putting-music-discovery-at-the-forefront |title=Universal Music Group |website=Universalmusic.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universalmusic.com/corporate/news35666 |title=Universal Music Group |website=Universalmusic.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref><ref>[https://archive.is/20130205212016/http://www.vodafone.com/content/index/press/group_press_releases/2005/press_release14_11.html]</ref><ref>[https://archive.is/20120721231115/http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/news/e3ia2bdd85a040b9b018e243e2f9e6ae94f ]</ref> Grainge led the 2017 multi-year global license agreement between UMG and Spotify.<ref name=\"umg spotify\">{{cite web |title=SPOTIFY AND UNIVERSAL MUSIC GROUP ANNOUNCE GLOBAL, MULTI-YEAR LICENSE AGREEMENT - UMG |url=https://www.universalmusic.com/spotify-and-universal-music-group-announce-global-multi-year-license-agreement/ |website=UMG |accessdate=23 August 2018 |date=4 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nGrainge led the acquisition of Bravado, then part of Sanctuary, and transformed it into UMG's entertainment merchandising and brand management division, Bravado. The company represents artists including [[Justin Bieber]], [[Lady Gaga]], and [[Kanye West]], and has formed partnerships with retailers including Barneys, Bloomingdale's and Selfridge's.<ref name=\"sanctuary\">{{cite web |last1=Allen |first1=Katie |title=Universal buys troubled Sanctuary for \u00a344.5m |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2007/aug/03/music |website=the Guardian |accessdate=23 August 2018 |language=en |date=3 August 2007}}</ref><ref name=\"ny times\">{{cite web |last1=Safronova |first1=Valeriya |title=Maestros of the Concert Merchandise Movement |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/25/fashion/weeknd-gaga-kanye-west-justin-bieber-concert-merch.html |website=NY Times |accessdate=23 August 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"bloomingdales\">{{cite web |last1=Lockwood |first1=Lisa |title=Bloomingdale\u2019s Teams With Universal Music Group and Bravado for Major Retail Promotion |url=https://wwd.com/business-news/retail/bloomingdales-teams-with-universal-music-group-and-bravado-for-major-retail-promotion-11083718/ |website=WWD |accessdate=23 August 2018 |date=4 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"evening standard\">{{cite web |last1=Randhawa |first1=Kiran |title=A Rolling Stones pop-up shop is coming to Selfridges |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/london-life/rolling-stones-selfridges-a3833556.html |website=Evening Standard |accessdate=23 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nGrainge also oversaw the expansion of classical labels [[Deutsche Grammophon]] and [[Decca Classics]], and agreed a global strategic partnership with entertainment company [[Live Nation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universalmusic.com/corporate/live-nation-entertainment-and-universal-music-group-announce-strategic-partnership |title=Universal Music Group |website=Universalmusic.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, UMG was worth $22 billion, triple what it was worth when Grainge took over at the company.<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web |last1=Parisi |first1=Paula |title=Universal Music Group\u2019s Value Triples to $22 Billion Under Lucian Grainge |url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/universal-music-group-valuation-lucian-grainge-1202400328/ |website=Variety |accessdate=23 August 2018 |date=27 April 2017}}</ref> In July 2018, [[JPMorgan]] said that UMG could be worth as much as $40 billion<ref name=\"ny post\">{{cite web |last1=Steigrad |first1=Alexandra |title=Universal Music Group won\u2019t go public |url=https://nypost.com/2018/07/30/universal-music-group-wont-go-public/ |website=New York Post |accessdate=23 August 2018 |date=31 July 2018}}</ref> and then increased the valuation to $50 billion in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/universal-music-group-valuation-hits-50bn-as-vivendi-seeks-half-dozen-investment-bank-partners/|title=Universal Music Group valuation hits $50bn \u2013 as Vivendi seeks 'half dozen' investment bank partners|date=2019-02-18|website=Music Business Worldwide|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Vivendi announced that Grainge had agreed to extend his tenure as UMG's chairman and CEO until at least 2020, stating he was key to its strategy.<ref>{{cite web|title = Vivendi: Five-year development plan for Universal Music Group \u2013 Lucian Grainge committed to UMG and Vivendi at least until 2020 {{!}} Vivendi|url = http://www.vivendi.com/investment-analysts/press-releases/vivendi-five-year-development-plan-for-universal-music-group-lucian-grainge-committed-to-umg-and-vivendi-at-least-until-2020/|website = www.vivendi.com|accessdate = 2015-09-21}}</ref> Under his management, UMG experienced growth in annual revenue, digital recorded music revenue and EBITDA.<ref>{{cite web|title = Lucian Grainge signs new deal with Universal Music Group - Music Business Worldwide|url = http://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/lucian-grainge-signs-new-deal-universal-music-group/|accessdate = 2015-09-21}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn January 1993, Grainge married his first wife, attorney Samantha Berg. That November, she experienced complications while giving birth to their son, and fell into a coma from which she never recovered.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-420086/Take-That-concert---13-year-olds-birthday-party.html | location=London | work=Daily Mail | title=Take That in concert.... for 13-year-old's birthday party | date=2 December 2006}}</ref> She died in England in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://search.ancestry.com/cgi-bin/sse.dll?rank=1&new=1&MSAV=0&msT=1&gss=angs-c&gsfn=Samantha&gsln=Grainge&uidh=000&pcat=34&h=1022006357&db=ONSDeath93&indiv=1&requr=301056688132&ur=32768 |title=Join Ancestry |website=Search.ancestry.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002, Grainge married his second wife, Caroline. Their daughter was born in 2001. In November 2012 Grainge and his wife reportedly paid US$13 million for a house in [[Pacific Palisades, Los Angeles|Pacific Palisades]]. They had previously leased a [[Brentwood, Los Angeles|Brentwood]] home from the owner of [[Rhino Entertainment]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://realestalker.blogspot.com/2013/08/south-parks-trey-parker-buys-big.html |title=The Real Estalker: South Park's Trey Parker Buys Big Brentwood Digs |website=Realestalker.blogspot.com |date=2013-08-07 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref>\n\nHis older brother was [[Nigel Grainge]], the founder of Ensign Records.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/nigel-grainge-obituary-hpz88mt5r |title=Nigel Grainge &#124; Register |website=Thetimes.co.uk |date=2017-06-17 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref>\n\n==Honours and awards==\nIn 2008, Grainge received the [[Music Industry Trusts' Award]], which recognises the world's most successful music executives. The award was presented by members of U2, and Take That performed at the ceremony.\n \nGrainge was appointed [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] (CBE) in the 2010 New Year Honours for services to the creative industries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vivendi.org/vivendi/Lucian-Grainge |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-11-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918022041/http://www.vivendi.org/vivendi/Lucian-Grainge |archivedate=18 September 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 2012, he was appointed a British Business Ambassador by the UK Prime Minister [[David Cameron]].<ref>{{cite web |title=City Spy: Lucian Grainge is selling UK to Hollywood |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/business/cityspy/city-spy-lucian-grainge-is-selling-uk-to-hollywood-8455392.html |website=London Evening Standard |accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Spanier |first1=Gideon |title=Lucian Grainge: Banging the drum for the UK in LA |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/analysis-and-features/lucian-grainge-banging-the-drum-for-the-uk-in-la-8488078.html |website=The Independent |accessdate=19 February 2019 |language=en |date=8 February 2013}}</ref> He was [[Knight Bachelor|knighted]] in the 2016 Birthday Honours for services to British business and inward investment.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=61608|supp=y|page=B2|date=11 June 2016}}</ref> He was inaugurated to appointment to the Order of the British Empire and Knight Bachelor by [[Prince William]] on November 29, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Universal Music Chairman Lucian Grainge Knighted By Prince William|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/7595826/lucian-grainge-knighthood-photo-umg|website=Billboard|accessdate=30 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nGrainge is a trustee of the American Friends of The Royal Foundation of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge and Prince Harry.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sir Lucian Grainge  Songwriters Hall of Fame |url=https://www.songhall.org/awards/winner/sir_lucian_grainge |website=Songwriters Hall of Fame |accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, he received the Humanitarian Award from [[The Foundation for Ethnic Understanding]]. That same year, UMG was honoured with a SAG-AFTRA American Scene Award, recognising the company's commitment to diversity as exemplified by its \"entire catalog and roster of artists.\"<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.sagaftra.org/sag-aftra-announces-american-scene-award-recipients |title= SAG-AFTRA Announces American Scene Award Recipients |publisher= SAG-AFTRA One Union}}</ref> In 2014, he was awarded the President's Merit Award (\"Icon Award\") by the [[Grammy Award]] in recognition of his significant contributions to the music industry.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.grammy.com/news/pre-grammy-gala-to-honor-lucian-grainge|title= Pre-GRAMMY Gala To Honor Lucian Grainge |publisher= GRAMMY.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/legal-and-management/5885327/lucian-grainge-receives-icon-award-at-clive-davis-pre\n|title= Lucian Grainge Receives Icon Award at Clive Davis' Pre-Grammy Gala As Music Industry Looks On |publisher= Billboard}}</ref> In 2015, he received the Spirit of Life Award from the City of Hope, awarded for outstanding achievements in business and dedication to philanthropic causes.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6516963/lucian-grainge-city-of-hope-spirit-of-life-award |title= Lucian Grainge to Receive City of Hope Spirit of Life Award |publisher= Billboard}}</ref>\n\nGrainge serves on the boards of [[Lionsgate]] and [[Northeastern University]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ingham|first1=Tim|title=Lucian Grainge is now a Director at Lionsgate (and still boss of UMG) - Music Business Worldwide|url=http://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/lucian-grainge-now-director-lionsgate-still-boss-umg/|website=Music Business Worldwide|accessdate=18 October 2016|date=14 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.northeastern.edu/neuhome/about/trustees.html |title= Members of the Corporation 2013\u20132014 |publisher= Northeastern University}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Grainge was featured in ''[[Amy (2015 film)|Amy]]'', a [[documentary film]] depicting the life and death of British singer [[Amy Winehouse]].\n\nIn October 2016, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' presented Grainge with its 2016 Empowerment Award for overseeing a \"noticeable shift in the demographics of the industry leader\u2019s C-suites\" with women occupying some of the highest executive positions at Universal Music Group.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Barker|first1=Andrew|title=Universal Music Group\u2019s Lucian Grainge Serves as a Champion of Female Leadership|url=https://variety.com/2016/music/features/lucian-grainge-universal-music-group-female-leadership-1201884268/|website=Variety|accessdate=18 October 2016|date=11 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, the [[Cannes Lions International Festival of Creativity]] announced that Grainge would be honored as the 2017 Media Person of the Year, the first music executive to receive this honour.<ref name=\"Cannes\">{{cite web|title=Sir Lucian Grainge named Cannes Lions Media Person of the Year 2017|url=https://www.canneslions.com/just-announced/2017/may-17/01/sir-lucian-grainge-named-cannes-lions-media-person-of-the-year-2017#/|website=Canneslions.com|accessdate=22 May 2017|language=en}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Philip Thomas, CEO of Ascential Events, organizers of Cannes Lions, praised his \"bold investments in music and technology that helped return the industry to growth, while continuing to foster an environment that puts artists first\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Iasimone |first1=Ashley |title=Sir Lucian Grainge, UMG Chairman & CEO, Named Cannes Lions Media Person of the Year |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7776968/sir-lucian-grainge-cannes-lions-media-person-of-the-year-2017 |website=Billboard |accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, Grainge was inducted into the [[Songwriters Hall of Fame]] with the Howie Richmond Hitmaker award. At the ceremony, [[Ariana Grande]] performed in his honor and Grainge was inducted by [[The Weeknd]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Duffy |first1=Thom |title=Universal's Lucian Grainge Honored By Songwriters Hall of Fame: Read His Acceptance Speech |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8461167/lucian-grainge-honored-songwriters-hall-of-fame-read-speech |website=Billboard |accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe was awarded an honorary doctorate of music by the [[Berklee College of Music]] in May 2016<ref>{{cite web|author=By&nbsp; Allen Bush |url=https://www.berklee.edu/news/rita-morno-isley-brothers-lucian-grainge-milton-nascimento-honored-berklee-commencement |title=Rita Moreno, the Isley Brothers, Lucian Grainge, Milton Nascimento Honored at Commencement &#124; Berklee College of Music |website=Berklee.edu |date=2016-05-07 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref> and an honorary doctorate of global commerce by [[Northeastern University]] in May 2017.<ref name=\"Northeastern\">{{cite web|title=Northeastern announces 2017 honorary degree recipients|url=http://news.northeastern.edu/2017/05/northeastern-announces-2017-honorary-degree-recipients/|website=News @ Northeastern|accessdate=22 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, Grainge received a [[PTTOW!]] Icon Award, which \"honors trailblazers in their industries who have had an impact on culture around the world.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hitsdailydouble.com/news&id=315812&title+PTTOW!-DECLARES-GRAINGE-AN-ICON|title=HITS Daily Double : Rumor Mill - PTTOW! DECLARES GRAINGE AN ICON|website=HITS Daily Double|language=en|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref>\n\n''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' named Grainge as the first-ever Executive of the Decade after he topped the magazine's \"Power 100\" list as the most powerful person in the music business in 2013, 2015, 2016, and 2019.<ref name=\"2019 power 100\">{{cite web |last1=Marks |first1=Craig |title=Billboard Power 100's New No. 1: Universal Music Group's Lucian Grainge |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8496609/power-100-lucian-grainge-no-1-universal-music-group |website=Billboard |accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8548431/lucian-grainge-power-executive-of-the-decade-interview|title=Lucian Grainge of Universal Music Group: Executive of the Decade|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> He is the only person to ever hold that distinction more than once and for consecutive years.<ref name=\"Billboard\"/><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/1536345/billboard-reveals-the-2013-power-100 |title= Billboard Reveals the 2013 Power 100 |publisher= Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Staff|title=No. 1: Lucian Grainge {{!}} Power 100|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/6874748/no-1-lucian-grainge-power-100|website=Billboard|accessdate=22 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Irving Azoff]] called him \"'the great hope for the music business'\" and [[Jimmy Iovine]] commented that Grainge \"is working to restore [a] spirit of risk-taking and innovation\" by being \"'willing and open to entrepreneurship and that kind of thing the record industry has gotten depleted of.'\"<ref name=\"Los Angeles Times\">{{cite web |url= http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-fi-ct-music-business-change-20140309,0,1977338.story#axzz2vTBwLiTa |title= Can this man save the music business? |publisher= Los Angeles Times}}</ref> An interview feature in ''Billboard'' described Grainge as \"a fierce and tireless advocate for the recorded-music business\".<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/1538532/billboard-power-100-lucian-grainge-qa |title= Billboard Power 100: Lucian Grainge Q&A |publisher= Billboard}}</ref> In 2013, CNET wrote that \u201cGrainge is positioning Universal to lead the pack\u201d of major labels in their embracing of new digital opportunities.<ref name=\"CNET\">{{cite web |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-1023_3-57594963-93/crank-it-up-russell-simmons-universal-music-launch-label-on-youtube/ |title=Crank it up: Russell Simmons, Universal Music launch label \u2013 on YouTube|publisher= CNET}}</ref> A 2014 front-page ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' profile said that \"if anyone can save the music business, it might be Grainge.\"<ref name=\"Los Angeles Times\"/>\n\nIn January 2020, Grainge was awarded a star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]] with UMG artists including [[Beck]], [[Justin Bieber]], [[Birdman (rapper)|Birdman]], [[Lewis Capaldi]], [[Tori Kelly]], [[Sam Smith]], and [[Hailee Steinfeld]] in attendance. [[Shawn Mendes]] and [[Lionel Richie]] were the ceremony's featured presenters. [[Ellen K]] of [[KOST]] Radio Morning Show host, the emcee of the event, said, \"I've never seen so many stars show up to a Walk of Fame ceremony before.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/record-labels/8548910/universal-music-ceo-lucian-grainge-toasted-by-shawn-mendes|title=Universal Music CEO Lucian Grainge Toasted by Shawn Mendes & More at Hollywood Walk of Fame Ceremony|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/e3i6c8a99484479c6fe47cc255d753293b0 The Rise of Lucian Grainge]\n*[https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2009/aug/25/mandelson-web-cutoff-plan-attacked Mandelson web cutoff plan 'potentially illegal']\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{succession box\n  | before = [[Doug Morris]]\n  | title  = Chairman & Chief Executive Officer of [[Universal Music Group]]\n  | years  = 1 January 2011 to Present\n  | after  = incumbent\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grainge, Lucian}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:British music industry executives]]\n[[Category:American music industry executives]]\n[[Category:Universal Music Group]]\n[[Category:Commanders of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Knights Bachelor]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople awarded knighthoods]]\n[[Category:People from Pacific Palisades, Los Angeles]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=September 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- For individuals; see Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                = Sir Lucian Grainge\n| image                 =\n| alt             = \n| caption            = \n| image_size            = \n| background          = non_performing_personnel\n| birth_name          = Lucian Charles Grainge\n| alias               = \n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1960|2|29}}\n| birth_place         = {{Nowrap|London, England, United Kingdom}}\n| origin              = \n| instrument          = \n| genre               = \n| occupation          = Chairman & chief executive officer, [[Universal Music Group]]\n| years_active        = 1982\u2013present \n| label               = [[Universal Music Group]]\n| associated_acts     = \n| website                 = \n}}\n\n'''Sir Lucian Charles Grainge''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CBE}} (born 29 February 1960)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people/people-of-today/people-of-today-search-results.aspx?personId=22650&name=Lucian+Charles |title=Debrett's - The trusted source on British social skills, etiquette and style-Debrett's |website=Debretts.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref> is the chairman and chief executive officer of [[Universal Music Group]]. Over the course of his career, he has worked with artists including [[Amy Winehouse]], [[ABBA]], [[Eurythmics]], [[Rihanna (singer)|Rihanna]], [[Sam Smith (singer)|Sam Smith]], [[Take That]], [[Psychedelic Furs]], [[The Rolling Stones]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Jamie Cullum]] and [[Andrea Bocelli]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.grammy.com/news/pre-grammy-gala-to-honor-lucian-grainge|title= Pre-GRAMMY Gala To Honor Lucian Grainge |publisher= Grammy.com}}</ref><ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web |url= https://www.billboard.com/biz/6465255/lucian-grainge-the-2015-billboard-power-100 |title= Lucian Grainge: The 2015 Billboard Power 100 |publisher= Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.fmqb.com/article.asp?id=2891913 |title= Lucian Grainge Tops Billboard's 2015 Power 100 List |publisher= FMQB}}</ref> Grainge has worked in the music business for his entire career.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news| url=http://www.time.com/time/business/article/0,8599,1967817,00.html | work=Time | title=New Boss for Universal Music, Lady Gaga Record Label \u2013 TIME | date=3 March 2010}}</ref> Billboard magazine named Grainge as the most powerful person in the music business on four occasions in the 2010s, and the first-ever Executive of the Decade.<ref name=\"2019 power 100\">{{cite web |last1=Marks |first1=Craig |title=Billboard Power 100's New No. 1: Universal Music Group's Lucian Grainge |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8496609/power-100-lucian-grainge-no-1-universal-music-group |website=Billboard |accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8548431/lucian-grainge-power-executive-of-the-decade-interview|title=Lucian Grainge of Universal Music Group: Executive of the Decade|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> \n\n==Early life and career==\nGrainge grew up in [[North London]]. He was raised Jewish.<ref>https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/sir-lucian-grainge-we-must-keep-listening-to-new-ideas-through-young-ears/</ref> Grainge left [[Queen Elizabeth's Grammar School for Boys]] at the age of 18, and began working as a runner at MPC, a talent scout company.<ref name=autogenerated1 /> After contacting several record label bosses, he was offered a job by [[Maurice Oberstein]], chairman of [[CBS Records]], working at publishing company April Music's A&R department. His first signing was [[The Psychedelic Furs]]. In 1982, he became the director of [[RCA Music]] Publishing. Two years later he became an A&R director for [[MCA Records]]. He set up PolyGram Music Publishing in 1986 and joined Polydor as general manager of A&R and business affairs in 1993. He was promoted to managing director of Polydor in 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/news/e3i6c8a99484479c6fe47cc255d753293b0 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-11-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110907164645/http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/news/e3i6c8a99484479c6fe47cc255d753293b0 |archivedate=7 September 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> \n\n==Universal Music Group==\nGrainge became the chairman of the UK division of the Universal Music Group, and then in 2005 of Universal Music Group International. He served in this position until 2010. On 1 January 2011 he became CEO of Universal Music Group, and then chairman on 9 March 2011, succeeding [[Doug Morris]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universalmusic.com/corporate/news35723 |title=Universal Music Group |website=Universalmusic.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref>\n\nWithin his first year as chairman & CEO of Universal, the company acquired [[EMI]]'s Recorded Music operations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/record-labels/emi-publishing-goes-to-sony-label-to-universal-1005508552.story |title=EMI Publishing Goes to Sony, Label to Universal &#124; Billboard |website=Billboard.biz |date=2011-11-11 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref> Grainge argued that selling to Universal was the only way to improve EMI, for the benefit of the entire industry.<ref name=\"Buzzfeed\">{{cite web |url = https://www.buzzfeed.com/richardmorgan/how-universal-music-ceo-lucian-grainge-became-the-most-power|title= How Universal Music CEO Lucian Grainge Became The Most Powerful Man in Music |publisher= Buzzfeed}}</ref> UMG subsequently attempted to revitalise former EMI labels including Capitol Records and Virgin Records.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/1083683/universal-music-ceo-lucian-grainge-says-hell-double-ar-investment-at |title=Universal Music CEO Lucian Grainge Says He'll 'Double A&R Investment' at Capitol, Virgin |publisher= Billboard}}</ref> Commenting on the EMI acquisition, [[Buzzfeed]] commented that \"Grainge will go down as the master architect of what is likely to be the last big deal in the music business\".<ref name=\"Buzzfeed\"/>\n\nAs chairman and Chief Executive of Universal, Grainge has also sought to increase the group's international digital expansion via distribution partnerships with technology companies, including [[Apple Inc.|Apple]], [[Spotify]], [[Facebook]], [[Tencent]], and [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/digital-and-mobile/apple-signs-deal-with-universal-music-group-1005213452.story |title=Apple Signs Deal With Universal Music Group for iCloud, Major Publishers Also on Board &#124; Billboard |website=Billboard.biz |date=2011-06-02 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/digital-and-mobile/universal-music-group-launching-spotify-1005293772.story |title=Universal Music Group Launching Spotify Playlist Service for U.S. Fans &#124; Billboard |website=Billboard.biz |date=2011-07-27 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20101001085211/http://corporate.sky.com/media/press_releases/2008/sky_to_partner_with_universal_music_for_innovative_new_digital_music_service.htm]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universalmusic.com/corporate/universal-music-group-expands-digsterfm-with-rdio-putting-music-discovery-at-the-forefront |title=Universal Music Group |website=Universalmusic.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universalmusic.com/corporate/news35666 |title=Universal Music Group |website=Universalmusic.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref><ref>[https://archive.is/20130205212016/http://www.vodafone.com/content/index/press/group_press_releases/2005/press_release14_11.html]</ref><ref>[https://archive.is/20120721231115/http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/news/e3ia2bdd85a040b9b018e243e2f9e6ae94f ]</ref> Grainge led the 2017 multi-year global license agreement between UMG and Spotify.<ref name=\"umg spotify\">{{cite web |title=SPOTIFY AND UNIVERSAL MUSIC GROUP ANNOUNCE GLOBAL, MULTI-YEAR LICENSE AGREEMENT - UMG |url=https://www.universalmusic.com/spotify-and-universal-music-group-announce-global-multi-year-license-agreement/ |website=UMG |accessdate=23 August 2018 |date=4 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nGrainge led the acquisition of Bravado, then part of Sanctuary, and transformed it into UMG's entertainment merchandising and brand management division, Bravado. The company represents artists including [[Justin Bieber]], [[Lady Gaga]], and [[Kanye West]], and has formed partnerships with retailers including Barneys, Bloomingdale's and Selfridge's.<ref name=\"sanctuary\">{{cite web |last1=Allen |first1=Katie |title=Universal buys troubled Sanctuary for \u00a344.5m |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2007/aug/03/music |website=the Guardian |accessdate=23 August 2018 |language=en |date=3 August 2007}}</ref><ref name=\"ny times\">{{cite web |last1=Safronova |first1=Valeriya |title=Maestros of the Concert Merchandise Movement |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/25/fashion/weeknd-gaga-kanye-west-justin-bieber-concert-merch.html |website=NY Times |accessdate=23 August 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"bloomingdales\">{{cite web |last1=Lockwood |first1=Lisa |title=Bloomingdale\u2019s Teams With Universal Music Group and Bravado for Major Retail Promotion |url=https://wwd.com/business-news/retail/bloomingdales-teams-with-universal-music-group-and-bravado-for-major-retail-promotion-11083718/ |website=WWD |accessdate=23 August 2018 |date=4 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"evening standard\">{{cite web |last1=Randhawa |first1=Kiran |title=A Rolling Stones pop-up shop is coming to Selfridges |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/london-life/rolling-stones-selfridges-a3833556.html |website=Evening Standard |accessdate=23 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nGrainge also oversaw the expansion of classical labels [[Deutsche Grammophon]] and [[Decca Classics]], and agreed a global strategic partnership with entertainment company [[Live Nation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universalmusic.com/corporate/live-nation-entertainment-and-universal-music-group-announce-strategic-partnership |title=Universal Music Group |website=Universalmusic.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, UMG was worth $22 billion, triple what it was worth when Grainge took over at the company.<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web |last1=Parisi |first1=Paula |title=Universal Music Group\u2019s Value Triples to $22 Billion Under Lucian Grainge |url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/universal-music-group-valuation-lucian-grainge-1202400328/ |website=Variety |accessdate=23 August 2018 |date=27 April 2017}}</ref> In July 2018, [[JPMorgan]] said that UMG could be worth as much as $40 billion<ref name=\"ny post\">{{cite web |last1=Steigrad |first1=Alexandra |title=Universal Music Group won\u2019t go public |url=https://nypost.com/2018/07/30/universal-music-group-wont-go-public/ |website=New York Post |accessdate=23 August 2018 |date=31 July 2018}}</ref> and then increased the valuation to $50 billion in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/universal-music-group-valuation-hits-50bn-as-vivendi-seeks-half-dozen-investment-bank-partners/|title=Universal Music Group valuation hits $50bn \u2013 as Vivendi seeks 'half dozen' investment bank partners|date=2019-02-18|website=Music Business Worldwide|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Vivendi announced that Grainge had agreed to extend his tenure as UMG's chairman and CEO until at least 2020, stating he was key to its strategy.<ref>{{cite web|title = Vivendi: Five-year development plan for Universal Music Group \u2013 Lucian Grainge committed to UMG and Vivendi at least until 2020 {{!}} Vivendi|url = http://www.vivendi.com/investment-analysts/press-releases/vivendi-five-year-development-plan-for-universal-music-group-lucian-grainge-committed-to-umg-and-vivendi-at-least-until-2020/|website = www.vivendi.com|accessdate = 2015-09-21}}</ref> Under his management, UMG experienced growth in annual revenue, digital recorded music revenue and EBITDA.<ref>{{cite web|title = Lucian Grainge signs new deal with Universal Music Group - Music Business Worldwide|url = http://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/lucian-grainge-signs-new-deal-universal-music-group/|accessdate = 2015-09-21}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn January 1993, Grainge married his first wife, attorney Samantha Berg. That November, she experienced complications while giving birth to their son, and fell into a coma from which she never recovered.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-420086/Take-That-concert---13-year-olds-birthday-party.html | location=London | work=Daily Mail | title=Take That in concert.... for 13-year-old's birthday party | date=2 December 2006}}</ref> She died in England in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://search.ancestry.com/cgi-bin/sse.dll?rank=1&new=1&MSAV=0&msT=1&gss=angs-c&gsfn=Samantha&gsln=Grainge&uidh=000&pcat=34&h=1022006357&db=ONSDeath93&indiv=1&requr=301056688132&ur=32768 |title=Join Ancestry |website=Search.ancestry.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002, Grainge married his second wife, Caroline. Their daughter was born in 2001. In November 2012 Grainge and his wife reportedly paid US$13 million for a house in [[Pacific Palisades, Los Angeles|Pacific Palisades]]. They had previously leased a [[Brentwood, Los Angeles|Brentwood]] home from the owner of [[Rhino Entertainment]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://realestalker.blogspot.com/2013/08/south-parks-trey-parker-buys-big.html |title=The Real Estalker: South Park's Trey Parker Buys Big Brentwood Digs |website=Realestalker.blogspot.com |date=2013-08-07 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref>\n\nHis older brother was [[Nigel Grainge]], the founder of Ensign Records.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/nigel-grainge-obituary-hpz88mt5r |title=Nigel Grainge &#124; Register |website=Thetimes.co.uk |date=2017-06-17 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref>\n\n==Honours and awards==\nIn 2008, Grainge received the [[Music Industry Trusts' Award]], which recognises the world's most successful music executives. The award was presented by members of U2, and Take That performed at the ceremony.\n \nGrainge was appointed [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] (CBE) in the 2010 New Year Honours for services to the creative industries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vivendi.org/vivendi/Lucian-Grainge |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-11-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918022041/http://www.vivendi.org/vivendi/Lucian-Grainge |archivedate=18 September 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 2012, he was appointed a British Business Ambassador by the UK Prime Minister [[David Cameron]].<ref>{{cite web |title=City Spy: Lucian Grainge is selling UK to Hollywood |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/business/cityspy/city-spy-lucian-grainge-is-selling-uk-to-hollywood-8455392.html |website=London Evening Standard |accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Spanier |first1=Gideon |title=Lucian Grainge: Banging the drum for the UK in LA |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/analysis-and-features/lucian-grainge-banging-the-drum-for-the-uk-in-la-8488078.html |website=The Independent |accessdate=19 February 2019 |language=en |date=8 February 2013}}</ref> He was [[Knight Bachelor|knighted]] in the 2016 Birthday Honours for services to British business and inward investment.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=61608|supp=y|page=B2|date=11 June 2016}}</ref> He was inaugurated to appointment to the Order of the British Empire and Knight Bachelor by [[Prince William]] on November 29, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Universal Music Chairman Lucian Grainge Knighted By Prince William|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/7595826/lucian-grainge-knighthood-photo-umg|website=Billboard|accessdate=30 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nGrainge is a trustee of the American Friends of The Royal Foundation of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge and Prince Harry.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sir Lucian Grainge  Songwriters Hall of Fame |url=https://www.songhall.org/awards/winner/sir_lucian_grainge |website=Songwriters Hall of Fame |accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, he received the Humanitarian Award from [[The Foundation for Ethnic Understanding]]. That same year, UMG was honoured with a SAG-AFTRA American Scene Award, recognising the company's commitment to diversity as exemplified by its \"entire catalog and roster of artists.\"<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.sagaftra.org/sag-aftra-announces-american-scene-award-recipients |title= SAG-AFTRA Announces American Scene Award Recipients |publisher= SAG-AFTRA One Union}}</ref> In 2014, he was awarded the President's Merit Award (\"Icon Award\") by the [[Grammy Award]] in recognition of his significant contributions to the music industry.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.grammy.com/news/pre-grammy-gala-to-honor-lucian-grainge|title= Pre-GRAMMY Gala To Honor Lucian Grainge |publisher= GRAMMY.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/legal-and-management/5885327/lucian-grainge-receives-icon-award-at-clive-davis-pre\n|title= Lucian Grainge Receives Icon Award at Clive Davis' Pre-Grammy Gala As Music Industry Looks On |publisher= Billboard}}</ref> In 2015, he received the Spirit of Life Award from the City of Hope, awarded for outstanding achievements in business and dedication to philanthropic causes.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6516963/lucian-grainge-city-of-hope-spirit-of-life-award |title= Lucian Grainge to Receive City of Hope Spirit of Life Award |publisher= Billboard}}</ref>\n\nGrainge serves on the boards of [[Lionsgate]] and [[Northeastern University]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ingham|first1=Tim|title=Lucian Grainge is now a Director at Lionsgate (and still boss of UMG) - Music Business Worldwide|url=http://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/lucian-grainge-now-director-lionsgate-still-boss-umg/|website=Music Business Worldwide|accessdate=18 October 2016|date=14 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.northeastern.edu/neuhome/about/trustees.html |title= Members of the Corporation 2013\u20132014 |publisher= Northeastern University}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Grainge was featured in ''[[Amy (2015 film)|Amy]]'', a [[documentary film]] depicting the life and death of British singer [[Amy Winehouse]].\n\nIn October 2016, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' presented Grainge with its 2016 Empowerment Award for overseeing a \"noticeable shift in the demographics of the industry leader\u2019s C-suites\" with women occupying some of the highest executive positions at Universal Music Group.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Barker|first1=Andrew|title=Universal Music Group\u2019s Lucian Grainge Serves as a Champion of Female Leadership|url=https://variety.com/2016/music/features/lucian-grainge-universal-music-group-female-leadership-1201884268/|website=Variety|accessdate=18 October 2016|date=11 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, the [[Cannes Lions International Festival of Creativity]] announced that Grainge would be honored as the 2017 Media Person of the Year, the first music executive to receive this honour.<ref name=\"Cannes\">{{cite web|title=Sir Lucian Grainge named Cannes Lions Media Person of the Year 2017|url=https://www.canneslions.com/just-announced/2017/may-17/01/sir-lucian-grainge-named-cannes-lions-media-person-of-the-year-2017#/|website=Canneslions.com|accessdate=22 May 2017|language=en}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Philip Thomas, CEO of Ascential Events, organizers of Cannes Lions, praised his \"bold investments in music and technology that helped return the industry to growth, while continuing to foster an environment that puts artists first\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Iasimone |first1=Ashley |title=Sir Lucian Grainge, UMG Chairman & CEO, Named Cannes Lions Media Person of the Year |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7776968/sir-lucian-grainge-cannes-lions-media-person-of-the-year-2017 |website=Billboard |accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, Grainge was inducted into the [[Songwriters Hall of Fame]] with the Howie Richmond Hitmaker award. At the ceremony, [[Ariana Grande]] performed in his honor and Grainge was inducted by [[The Weeknd]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Duffy |first1=Thom |title=Universal's Lucian Grainge Honored By Songwriters Hall of Fame: Read His Acceptance Speech |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8461167/lucian-grainge-honored-songwriters-hall-of-fame-read-speech |website=Billboard |accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe was awarded an honorary doctorate of music by the [[Berklee College of Music]] in May 2016<ref>{{cite web|author=By&nbsp; Allen Bush |url=https://www.berklee.edu/news/rita-morno-isley-brothers-lucian-grainge-milton-nascimento-honored-berklee-commencement |title=Rita Moreno, the Isley Brothers, Lucian Grainge, Milton Nascimento Honored at Commencement &#124; Berklee College of Music |website=Berklee.edu |date=2016-05-07 |accessdate=2017-06-23}}</ref> and an honorary doctorate of global commerce by [[Northeastern University]] in May 2017.<ref name=\"Northeastern\">{{cite web|title=Northeastern announces 2017 honorary degree recipients|url=http://news.northeastern.edu/2017/05/northeastern-announces-2017-honorary-degree-recipients/|website=News @ Northeastern|accessdate=22 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, Grainge received a [[PTTOW!]] Icon Award, which \"honors trailblazers in their industries who have had an impact on culture around the world.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hitsdailydouble.com/news&id=315812&title+PTTOW!-DECLARES-GRAINGE-AN-ICON|title=HITS Daily Double : Rumor Mill - PTTOW! DECLARES GRAINGE AN ICON|website=HITS Daily Double|language=en|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref>\n\n''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' named Grainge as the first-ever Executive of the Decade after he topped the magazine's \"Power 100\" list as the most powerful person in the music business in 2013, 2015, 2016, and 2019.<ref name=\"2019 power 100\">{{cite web |last1=Marks |first1=Craig |title=Billboard Power 100's New No. 1: Universal Music Group's Lucian Grainge |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8496609/power-100-lucian-grainge-no-1-universal-music-group |website=Billboard |accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8548431/lucian-grainge-power-executive-of-the-decade-interview|title=Lucian Grainge of Universal Music Group: Executive of the Decade|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> He is the only person to ever hold that distinction more than once and for consecutive years.<ref name=\"Billboard\"/><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/1536345/billboard-reveals-the-2013-power-100 |title= Billboard Reveals the 2013 Power 100 |publisher= Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Staff|title=No. 1: Lucian Grainge {{!}} Power 100|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/6874748/no-1-lucian-grainge-power-100|website=Billboard|accessdate=22 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Irving Azoff]] called him \"'the great hope for the music business'\" and [[Jimmy Iovine]] commented that Grainge \"is working to restore [a] spirit of risk-taking and innovation\" by being \"'willing and open to entrepreneurship and that kind of thing the record industry has gotten depleted of.'\"<ref name=\"Los Angeles Times\">{{cite web |url= http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-fi-ct-music-business-change-20140309,0,1977338.story#axzz2vTBwLiTa |title= Can this man save the music business? |publisher= Los Angeles Times}}</ref> An interview feature in ''Billboard'' described Grainge as \"a fierce and tireless advocate for the recorded-music business\".<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/1538532/billboard-power-100-lucian-grainge-qa |title= Billboard Power 100: Lucian Grainge Q&A |publisher= Billboard}}</ref> In 2013, CNET wrote that \u201cGrainge is positioning Universal to lead the pack\u201d of major labels in their embracing of new digital opportunities.<ref name=\"CNET\">{{cite web |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-1023_3-57594963-93/crank-it-up-russell-simmons-universal-music-launch-label-on-youtube/ |title=Crank it up: Russell Simmons, Universal Music launch label \u2013 on YouTube|publisher= CNET}}</ref> A 2014 front-page ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' profile said that \"if anyone can save the music business, it might be Grainge.\"<ref name=\"Los Angeles Times\"/>\n\nIn January 2020, Grainge was awarded a star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]] with UMG artists including [[Beck]], [[Justin Bieber]], [[Birdman (rapper)|Birdman]], [[Lewis Capaldi]], [[Tori Kelly]], [[Sam Smith]], and [[Hailee Steinfeld]] in attendance. [[Shawn Mendes]] and [[Lionel Richie]] were the ceremony's featured presenters. [[Ellen K]] of [[KOST]] Radio Morning Show host, the emcee of the event, said, \"I've never seen so many stars show up to a Walk of Fame ceremony before.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/record-labels/8548910/universal-music-ceo-lucian-grainge-toasted-by-shawn-mendes|title=Universal Music CEO Lucian Grainge Toasted by Shawn Mendes & More at Hollywood Walk of Fame Ceremony|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/e3i6c8a99484479c6fe47cc255d753293b0 The Rise of Lucian Grainge]\n*[https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2009/aug/25/mandelson-web-cutoff-plan-attacked Mandelson web cutoff plan 'potentially illegal']\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{succession box\n  | before = [[Doug Morris]]\n  | title  = Chairman & Chief Executive Officer of [[Universal Music Group]]\n  | years  = 1 January 2011 to Present\n  | after  = incumbent\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grainge, Lucian}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:British music industry executives]]\n[[Category:American music industry executives]]\n[[Category:Universal Music Group]]\n[[Category:Commanders of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Knights Bachelor]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople awarded knighthoods]]\n[[Category:People from Pacific Palisades, Los Angeles]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toCBS Records(link changed toCBS Records International) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucian_Grainge"}
